From a45ace67deb1d20a3682b59ddb33bc3a19e838dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 31 Jul 2025 23:39:16 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK: CP: hostapd: ATF: add support for commitatf cli

Add hostapd_cli infra to pass all the commands for atf_offload module.
Implement commitatf command, which would send the dynamic enable flag
to driver and set the flag which would be used for starting
algorithm. Implemented get_commitatf command, used to display the
commitatf is set or cleared.

commitatf triggers the operation to enable ATF functionality in both
the driver and firmware. If ATF is not already enabled, activate it
during the commitatf. If ATF offload is enabled, initiate the airtime
allocation algorithm based on user-defined configurations. Start
airtime distribution for SSIDs, SSID groups, or peers, and
allocate airtime accordingly and send full update to FW with new
airtime allocation.

To enable ATF in firmware:
MLO:
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload commitatf {1/0}
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload  get_commitatf
Legacy:
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload commitatf {1/0}
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload  get_commitatf

Signed-off-by: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
